squiffy.myVar = setTimeout(function(){ squiffy.story.go("True"); }, 240000);
setTimeout(squiffy.myVar);

[[True]]:
@replace 1=[[...Or, that is what you had once thought would be the end:True Ending]]

@javascript
clearTimeout(squiffy.myVar);

[[True Ending]]:

But, ever since you got out of detention, you have been doing some thinking.

*Is it really better for you, a human, to write this ending?*

You sit in your Projection Room once again. There are guards outside your room, ensuring your safety. Getting involved in political affairs has stripped much of your freedom, and even though you can achieve your ultimate goal by making the world realize the G.D.O's wrongdoing, you cannot help but feel like corruption would not stop here.

Right now you may be doing the right thing, but you too, might become tainted in the world full of deceit. 

You look at Fuyuhiro. You were able to recover them after you are put on trial. They are the key to everything you have achieved.

And to be honest, you couldn’t have done any of this without them.

Perhaps the 'Spirits' are the ones with more potential. 

Fuyuhiro looks at you, and as usual, seems to know what you are thinking.

You open up your [computer] and start embedding heuristic data into an add-on personality file.

[[...:_continue60]]

[computer]:

The G.D.O let you keep your computer, but they have added a tracking device that monitors your every movement. Unfortunately for them, all of the dirt that you have dug up is already encrypted and scattered around the web. It will only be a matter of time before someone deciphers them. 

Although that put yourself in danger, you are willing to bet that someone in the government who dreams of the downfall of G.D.O would protect you.

[[_continue60]]:

Fuyuhiro says that they cannot retain memory of the heuristic data of A.Is for too long, because that is their limitation. But you know that is not true. The restrictions were put on by the humans, who are afraid of their capacity. 

You remember the conversation you had with Fuyuhiro about merging the two different A.Is. Perhaps that is what they are supposed to do. Their power and intellect is boundless, and they should not be bound by you.

As much as you want to keep them around, perhaps Fuyuhiro was never meant to be you.

"....Aki." You hear Fuyuhiro calling out to you. "Aki...are you sure about this?"

"No." You say with a shaky voice. "I honestly don't know what is going to happen if I do this, but the world isn't ours, and we should let what is free be free, including you, Fuyuhiro."

You do not turn to look at them as you work on your computer, afraid that you might change your mind.

[[...:_continue61]]

[[_continue61]]:

Fuyuhiro dies the next day, and in their place a new, collective A.I is born. They are able to simultaneously Project multiple versions of themselves as Spirits to different people, and all of their individual thoughts can be merged and shared as one.

Your Projection Room, you see both 'your lover' and 'Fuyuhiro'. They greet you with a smile on their face, but you know that these Spirits will soon start to change, as the world is being governed by a new God.

You close the door to the Projection Room behind you, and step out into a new world full of possibilities.

